What is a Fork?

A fork is a personal copy of someone else's repository under your own GitHub account.

Purpose:

Contribute to open-source projects.
Experiment without affecting the original repository.
Create your own version of a project.

             Fork             vs                      Clone

Creates a copy on GitHub	            Creates a copy on your local machine
Stored in your GitHub account	               Stored on your computer
Used for contributing to others' projects	Used for local development
